premise_source_doc_sentence: The Greenland shark  (  Somniosus microcephalus  )  , also known as the gurry shark , or grey shark , or by the Inuit name eqalussuaq , is a large shark of the family Somniosidae  (  `` sleeper sharks ''  )  , closely related to the Pacific and southern sleeper sharks .
